snippet.textDisplay: People who didn't watch him in his prime will never get this "artist" part. Sometimes he'd go 6-21, we wouldn't care. He had such a beautiful shot that we just loved seeing him take each of those 21 shots. The next day we'd go try to copy it. Sometimes out of nowhere and for no reason he'd cross the ball between his legs in each step as he brought the ball to halfcourt. That gave us a basketball drill to do for the next day. If I see a player do it today, I know he also went down to the backyard court and did the same Kobe drill the day I did it. When Kobe got hot and made 10 straight impossible shots he would become our superhero, he would even mesmerize his opponents, but most of the nights he was an earthly artist, he knew how to pull of his most aesthetic craft that you just wanted to try. There is no stats sheet to explain that. A superhero and an older brother at the same time.

snippet.textDisplay: I wasn’t a Kobe fan, but I have kind of a special weird connection — my family nickname is Koby, and there were always jokes and jeers accordingly. We’d always laugh when I’d shoot a basket and say “Kobe!”. Aside from that, I’ve loved the game of basketball as far back as I can remember, watching Kobe in his prime as a young boy in awe. My thoughts, prayers, and condolences have been pouring out to those that lost their lives and their families since I found out about the tragedy only an hour after it happened and will not be stopping anytime soon. Thank you, Kobe

snippet.textDisplay:
Only a few celebrities in history have had such a impact in our lives , sports and non sports , Kobe is up there with Michael Jackson , Elvis , 2pac , biggie ,prince , Whitney Houston , for us Hispanics Juan Gabriel and others like them, we have lost a hero a superhero, to some and ICON to others and a LEGEND to all of us 😢😢

Whether u liked the lakers or hated them , whether u liked basketball or not , KOBE will always be remembered for the impact he made on coaches ,teammates ,opponents and fans all over the world including in other sports who had the privilege and honor of just being in the same floor and arena with him .😭😭😢😢

The thing I have to say all the 👎 they don’t have a heart and should look at there loves ones ,kiss them and tell them they love them while they still can
with the passing of not just Kobe but also his 13yr old daughter and the rest of the passengers on the helicopter we should stop and think ,stuff like this should not happen but only god knows why they do
I’m a brother , son , uncle ,father and also a grandfather and I’ve had moments like this in my life and it’s never nice to go through this type of losses some I had a chance to say I love you and to others I didn’t 😢

The games that we watched of his and the lakers ,United everyone for a few hours a week to watch greatness in the making ,we got to see him do his magic on the court ,we forgot about our daily life troubles and stress for those few moments

the ones that got to see him play live in any arena throughout the nba and also the world while he played for team USA , cherish those memories and tell those stories to your kids and grandkids about how you had a chance to watch the greatest LAKER and one of the greatest players of all time play

We as fans only knew the player ,our hero our role model , we watched him fall and get back up so many times in and out of his basketball life , playing through personal problems and those damn basketball injuries
the players that played with him and against him seen a different side of him that we hear now with the stories they tell us .
Kobe the father we where just starting to see more of . That man loved his daughter’s so much !

8 MAMBA 🐍 FOREVER 24

snippet.textDisplay: Mamba mentality. Kobe.   As someone who grew up watching him and his growth and work effort I constantly drew reference to kobe mentally. If i was being a mailman I’d think if kobe were a mainlman he’d be the best one here so I’m gonna be the best one here. When I was younger and playing pickup and was able to pull off one of his ridiculous shots or fadeaways and a kid yelled kobe I’d be like you’re damn right, thats where I got it.  Whatever I’d work at in life, especially physical and athletic things I’d always think of how would Kobe approach this challenge. That winner attitude of I’m gonna find a way to get this done.  Kobe wasn’t perfect, but he was a good person, a passionate and curious person and a hero to his generation. Funny thing is he was my hero but never got his jersey cuz I hated the lakers, you can bet I’ve been sporting shoes shorts and hoodies the last decade though. RIP. I hope theres youth leagues in heaven you can coach your girl in.

snippet.textDisplay:
I didn't even like Kobe. Always rooted against that Kobe/Shaq dynasty...but Kobe had my respect due to his amazing drive and work ethic. He was old school and very respectful of past NBA greats. Even honoring them. He interviewed like MJ...very classy. He also won me over with his humor. His commercial with Jalen Rose is still one of the funniest sports bits I've seen.

Much respect and prayers to his family and everyone affected. I'll leave with this video Kobe made on former greats: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hI0DqGSNo04&feature=youtu.be
